<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Quicks recovery continues
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Despite a fall in turnover from Pounds 208.7m to Pounds 198.5m, Quicks
Group, the motor distributor, continued its recovery and finished 1992 with
pre-tax profits of Pounds 2.06m. This compared with previous losses of
Pounds 952,000.
Profits at halfway totalled Pounds 1.11m.
The year-end results were produced under accounting standard FRS 3. The 1991
figures were adjusted accordingly.
After tax of Pounds 738,000, compared with a Pounds 154,000 credit, earnings
per share were given as 7.8p (5.2p losses).
The dividend for the year is lifted to 4.5p (3p). This includes an increased
final of 2.75p.
