<HEADLINE>
FT  19 MAR 93 / UK Company News: Trio purchase beats forecast
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Martin Bierbaum, the international money broker, which was acquired for
Pounds 25.5m in January by Trio Investment Trust, recorded a pre-tax profit
ahead of forecasts at Pounds 7.04m in the year to September 30.
Over the same period the trust, now re-named Trio Holdings, posted a Pounds
68,000 pre-tax loss compared to a Pounds 73,000 profit in the previous year.
</TEXT>
<XX>
Companies:-
</XX>
<CO>Martin Bierbaum Group.
    Trio Holdings.
</CO>
<XX>
Countries:-
</XX>
<CN>GBZ  United Kingdom, EC.
</CN>
<XX>
Industries:-
</XX>
<IN>P6726 Investment Offices, NEC.
