FT  18 MAR 93 / Bildt wins economy confidence vote
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER BROWN-HUMES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   STOCKHOLM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
SWEDEN'S minority coalition government yesterday won a parliamentary vote of
confidence in its economic policies, averting the immediate threat of an
early general election, writes Christopher Brown- Humes in Stockholm.
The 23 members of the populist opposition New Democracy party, which last
week triggered the country's political crisis, abstained in the vote, which
the government won by 172 votes to 154.
