FT  18 MAR 93 / British Coal to study pit proposal
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ROBERT TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITISH Coal said last night it is to consider National Union of
Mineworkers' proposals to resolve the future of the 10 pits not included in
the current coal review by referring them to an independent body that could
report within 12 weeks, Robert Taylor writes.
Mr Kevan Hunt, British Coal employee relations director, said: 'While we
have some serious reservations, we will pursue the NUM proposals as a matter
of urgency.'
The decision follows a meeting yesterday between British Coal and the NUM at
which the union acknowledged that local and area consultation had taken
place over the future of the 10 collieries and proposed there should be no
national appeal over them.
