FT  18 MAR 93 / Observer: Watershed
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Is water polo dangerous? The risks clearly aren't confined to the one
immortalised by Tony Curtis when, impersonating an aqua-sporting millionaire
in Some like it Hot, he answered the question with: 'I should say so. Why,
the last time I played, I had three ponies drown right under me.'
The Red Stars water polo team from Yugoslavia have just been left high and
dry in South Africa because, in the opposite of a case of the biter bit, the
Pretoria government has endorsed the UN sanctions against their country.
They did manage one game on Monday, but the rest of their programme has gone
down the drain.
