time trying to get a proper assembly going again in Northern Ireland?' Mr
Paisley asked.
The Rev Martin Smyth, Ulster Unionist MP for Belfast south, said: 'If it was
a mistake, let him deliver the goods by creating an accountable democracy in
Northern Ireland.'
