</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
VENEZUELA has approved a finance ministry request to issue public-debt bonds
worth DM150m, Reuter reports from Caracas. The approval was given by a
senate committee and the funds will be used to refinance borrowings held by
two state-owned groups.
The two companies are Cadafe, a state utility, and the Caracas subway. The
refinancing will centre on borrowings that fell due last year or will fall
due this year.
The bulk of the issue, some DM126.26m, will be handled by BHF Bank of
Germany.
